        <prj:note>We propose to image two candidate tidal dwarf galaxies in CO (1-0) line in the Arp 305 system. The detections will give us CO morphologies, the H$_{2}$/H{\sc i} ratios and CO/H$_{\alpha}$ ratios to compare with other detected cases of TDGs, normal dwarfs and LSB galaxies. Additionally, one of the primary goals of this experiment is to look for signatures of a velocity gradient / rotation in one of our targets TDG1. ALMA's FWHM in this band and spatial resolution as well as our source's linear structure, relative isolation from the two main disks (NGC 4016/7), length of the major axis and H$_{\alpha}$ detections  make it a very suitable candidate to observe.
</prj:note>
